# SNS & fan-out

## SNS — pub/sub

Publish to a **topic** → SNS delivers a copy to **every subscriber** at once. **No queue** — persistence is the subscriber's job.

Subscribers: **SQS** (most common) · Lambda · HTTP webhooks · email / SMS / push · Firehose. Up to **12.5 M subs**; **filter policies** = each sub gets only what it cares about.

## SNS + SQS fan-out — the most reused pattern

One event → several downstreams, each at its own pace. Direct-to-many-queues couples the producer. Instead:

- Producer publishes **once** to an SNS topic
- SNS → each subscribed **SQS queue** → **independent consumer** (own DLQ, scaling)

**Producer doesn't know downstream** — add a consumer = 1 queue + 1 sub, no producer change; peers fail independently.
